[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Examining SVG and animation issues**\n\nI’m noticing potential issues with the BaseAnimationNode parse registers and the duration parsing; it looks like it needs to be set to 2000. There might be complications with AnimationPeriod start min value too. Also, I'm wondering if existing CSS classes on referenced rects apply correctly in SVG. If not, I think I should set the fill and stroke directly to avoid test failures. It seems better to use direct styles rather than relying entirely on class rules. There’s still a bit to clarify!\n\n**Considering SVG and CSS adjustments**\n\nI’m thinking about using references that create rects with fill for safety. It seems likely that the CSS ID selector is applied to the rects, so I might keep the class but also add `fill=\"#00cc00\"` and `stroke=\"#0000ff\"` directly to the use element. This way, the CSS still affects the circle. I need to ensure the pixel rect remains stable.\n\nAdditionally, there’s a potential issue regarding the gradient with objectBoundingBox. I should consider using `x2=\"100%\"` for more accurate coordinates in SVG. Let’s keep refining this!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0badab849ab5f46b016a00c0a9173481a3afb0bad2305311a1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAMCy7CHcJylbBe1CObrfWmFRMG7XV4L1QeH0R-_tl0NqmQv3fTsQZmQ9yz9Bm23JhoIUEHWHDZ0w-_IravewJ82-TGvqkTqdieJcogeSNtqTO-Tc3Ps7xwJzRBwAOkoR8Ddp1H4GjK5xGZ4gj1kTyrP9DGM3UNMA6PTeVhEczi561rWg6TnqZEKEeEU9eoxFy_PXy5F9ZweD3_Sf5vtJQhP1-CtikQFflVhjBcCeMr5bk270xIXBuLyoTPoNgWLjg5z_s9u2jm0rynoaai1mb7heknr8k3UUtHHdL-vSPttnW2iHt0JO2RRtn6-Mq2FJm4Te92ZaL6sn2j_KTAkRHuahoQpUnODHG-gBWP7GdnGPeHHQV2-L4xESve6lWgbC4FbbTmEi1j_aIauxO-iZFN7XQ0_Ag4XuK3jTTpZYCfH14-k5cQxz2B5XPbrUv3Y9OFQGCYI1kubmbmt1JV3ZYsXC58klB7cMRsruU8bL-ctljeL_Asjdn_qETzWPLmr-y1XFwni8_f9NxCTnoOF0fvSKYd0WvtyqHfO1gHdec7r4m_RjOrvEpY7rJTZWK2JZ04PFsxaPTXHsu11HrCfMKKfEkYqybQN6WCjftwhceDXjqU5t1V